<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Welcome to LETFs Data Validator</title>
    {{ template "includes" }}
</head>
<body>
<div>
    {{/* Side bar */}}
    {{ template "sidebar" }}
    {{/* Header */}}
    {{ template "header" }}
    {{/* Main Content */}}
    <div class="content-wrap">
        <div class="main">
            <div class="container-fluid">
                <h1 id="use-cases">Use Cases</h1>
                <section>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-12">
                            <div class="card">
                                <div class="card-title">
                                    <h2 id="tax-loss-harvesting">Tax Loss Harvesting</h2>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <p>Can I harvest my current losses in TECL, without losing exposure and triggering
                                        wash sales? Yes, you can! </p>
                                    <p>1 <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                                                    href="/letf-summary/TECL.html">TECL</a></span> = 1 <span
                                                class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/UPRO.html">UPRO</a></span>
                                        + 1 <span
                                                class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                                                    href="/letf-summary/TQQQ.html">TQQQ</a></span> (<a
                                                href="/letf-summary/overlaps/TECL_UPRO_TQQQ.html">72.53%
                                            combined overlap</a>)! </p>
                                    <h4 id="solve-how-many-shares-you-need-to-swap-with">Solve how many shares you need
                                        to swap with</h4>
                                    <p>(Number of shares of TECL owned) * (Price of TECL share) = X * (Price of UPRO
                                        share) + X * (Price of TQQQ
                                        share).</p>
                                    <p>Solve for X!</p>
                                    <p>On July 27th, 2020,</p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li><span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/TECL.html">TECL</a></span>
                                            is at $36.40
                                        </li>
                                        <li><span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/UPRO.html">UPRO</a></span>
                                            is at $41.39
                                        </li>
                                        <li><span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/TQQQ.html">TQQQ</a></span>
                                            is at $30.74
                                        </li>
                                        <li>I own 1385 shares, whose average purchase price is $50.00</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <p>Substituting we get </p>
                                    <p>36.40 * 1385 / (41.39 + 30.74) ~= 699 = X!</p>
                                    <h5 id="harvested-loss">Harvested Loss</h5>
                                    <p>While keeping approximately 73% of the same exposure, you&#39;ve captured
                                        approximately 18,836$ worth of tax losses
                                        which are not eligible for Wash Sale (assuming no more transactions on TECL)</p>
                                    <h3 id="example-2">Example 2</h3>
                                    <p>Sold 800 <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                                                    href="/letf-summary/FNGU.html">FNGU</a></span> at $9.45,</p>
                                    <p><span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                                                    href="/letf-summary/BULZ.html">BULZ</a></span> is at $5.31 and <span
                                                class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/UPRO.html">TQQQ</a></span>
                                        is at $30.74</p>
                                    <p>800 * 9.45 / (5.31 + 30.74) ~= 210</p>
                                    <p>So buy 210 <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                                                    href="/letf-summary/BULZ.html">BULZ</a></span> and 210 <span
                                                class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/TQQQ.html">TQQQ</a></span>
                                        shares
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-12">
                            <div class="card">
                                <div class="card-title">
                                    <h2 id="consolidation-themefication">Consolidation/Themefication</h2>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <p>Example: I own <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                                                    href="/stock-summary/SNDL.html">SNDL</a></span>, <span
                                                class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/stock-summary/TLRY.html">TLRY</a></span>,
                                        <span
                                                class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                                                    href="/stock-summary/CRON.html">CRON</a></span>. Can I replace the
                                        three holdings with an ETF? Yes.
                                        <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                                                    href="/stock-summary/POTX.html">POTX</a></span> has ~ 30% exposure
                                        to these stocks + other weed stocks
                                        :)</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-12">
                            <div class="card">
                                <div class="card-title">
                                    <h2 id="increase-leverage-">Increase Leverage!</h2>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <p>I own 100 shares of <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                                                    href="/letf-summary/SPY.html">SPY</a></span>, and I
                                        believe that <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                                                    href="/letf-summary/SPY.html">SPY</a></span> is going to
                                        increase. Let me dial up the leverage to 2x by adopting
                                        <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                                                    href="/letf-summary/QLD.html">QLD</a></span> and <span
                                                class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                                                    href="/letf-summary/SSO.html">SSO</a></span>.</p>
                                    <p>On July 26th, 2022: </p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li><span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/SPY.html">SPY</a></span>
                                            is at $390.90
                                        </li>
                                        <li><span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/QLD.html">QLD</a></span>
                                            is at $45.39
                                        </li>
                                        <li><span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a href="/letf-summary/SSO.html">SSO</a></span>
                                            is at $48.
                                        </li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <p>100 * 390 = X * 45.39 + X * 48</p>
                                    <p>X ~= 417. So you buy 417 shares of <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                                                    href="/letf-summary/QLD.html">QLD</a></span>
                                        and 417 shares of <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                                                    href="/letf-summary/SSO.html">SSO</a></span>.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-12">
                            <div class="card">
                                <div class="card-title">
                                    <h2 id="decrease-leverage-">Decrease Leverage!</h2>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <p>Reduce leverage from <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                                                    href="/letf-summary/SOXL.html">SOXL</a></span> to
                                        <span class="rounded_border letf_ticker"><a
                                                    href="/letf-summary/USD.html">USD</a></span> but still
                                        maintain exposure to <a href="/letf-summary/overlap/SOXL_USD.html">75%</a> of
                                        underlying stocks</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>
                <section id="stock_summary_footer">
                    {{ template "footer" }}
                </section>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
